Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:1011):
`stringifyPayload()` directly calls `JSON.stringify`. If the API ever returns a value containing a `bigint` or a circular reference (both will throw in `JSON.stringify`), the Deliveries drawer will error during render and can break the whole view. Consider wrapping this in a try/catch (and/or using a replacer that stringifies bigint) and returning a safe fallback string when serialization fails.

