Comment (src/views/__tests__/NotificationsView.spec.ts:1279):
This test asserts the rendered date contains the English locale string `May 22, 2026`, but `formatDate()` uses `new Intl.DateTimeFormat(undefined, ...)`, which is locale/timezone dependent in CI and can format as e.g. `22 May 2026` or shift the day based on TZ. To avoid flaky tests, stub `Intl.DateTimeFormat` / `formatDate`, or assert on a locale-agnostic signal (e.g., the ISO input value or just the year/time components).

Implementation guidance: In src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue, harden stringifyPayload(value: unknown) so the Deliveries drawer cannot throw during render. Replace the direct JSON.stringify(value, null, 2) call with a try/catch. Use a JSON.stringify replacer that converts typeof entry === 'bigint' to entry.toString(), and optionally tracks object references with a WeakSet so circular references render as a safe placeholder such as "[Circular]" instead of throwing. If serialization still fails, return a short safe fallback string like "Unable to display payload.". Keep sensitive-field sanitization unchanged; this function is only responsible for display serialization. Add or update a NotificationsView.spec.ts test that mounts/opens the job detail drawer with args or metadata containing a bigint and/or circular object, then asserts the drawer still renders and shows the safe serialized value/fallback instead of throwing.
Implementation guidance: In src/views/__tests__/NotificationsView.spec.ts, make the diagnostics date assertion locale-agnostic in the "renders diagnostics checks for digest, workflow, risk, and POAM notifications" test. The component's formatDate() uses Intl.DateTimeFormat(undefined, { dateStyle: 'medium', timeStyle: 'short' }), so do not assert the exact English text "May 22, 2026". Prefer asserting the diagnostics summary has a non-empty next-run value without relying on month wording, for example use a regex around "Next run:" that confirms it is not "Never" and includes stable components such as the year 2026, or stub Intl.DateTimeFormat in this spec to return a deterministic value before asserting that value. Avoid changing production formatDate() just to satisfy the test.
